==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wrangler
<hw>Wran"gler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An angry
disputant; one who disputes with heat or peevishness.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Noisy
and contentious <xex>wranglers</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>I.
Watts.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One of those who stand in the first rank of honors
in the University of Cambridge, England. They are called, according to
their rank, senior <xex>wrangler</xex>, second <xex>wrangler</xex>,
third <xex>wrangler</xex>, etc. Cf. <er>Optime</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wranglership</ent>⟦br⟧
